{"lemma":"ياقُوتَيْ","slug":"ياقُوتَيْ","root":"#.ق.ت","root_slug":"_-ق-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ق-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ياقُوت","root":"","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42488"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ruby"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sapphire"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Ultimately from Ancient Greek ὑάκινθος (huákinthos), possibly via Sogdian [script needed] (yγwth /⁠yaγūt⁠/, “ruby”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42488","headword_ar":"يَاقُوتٌ","root":"yqt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [coll. gen. n., The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sapphire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of whatever variety: the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruby, oriental ruby,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red sapphire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yAqwtN A^aHomaru","text_ar":"ياقوتٌ اَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of which there are several varieties, whereof one is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carbuncle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yAqwtN jamoriY~N","text_ar":"ياقوتٌ جَمْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sapphire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"commonly so called, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blue sapphire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yAqwtN A^azoraqu","text_ar":"ياقوتٌ اَزْرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"topaz, oriental topaz,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow sapphire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yAqwtN A^aSofaru","text_ar":"ياقوتٌ اَصْفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jacinth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hyacinth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Golius, who observes, as on the authority of the Teyfáshee, that by this name are called"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"various gems of the East;"},{"kind":"text","text":"four species thereof being enumerated; the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gold-coloured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"azure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"that the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sapphire"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chrysolite"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also thus called: but that, by the word used absolutely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red jacinth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hyacinth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"commonly called the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ruby,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is meant: which last remark is agreeable with modern usage:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well known gem;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) of which there are many varieties, (TA,) the most excellent whereof is that called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyAqwtu AlA^aHomaru Alr~um~aAniY~u","text_ar":"الياقوتُ الاَحْمَرُ الرُّمَّانِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbahoramaAniY~u","text_ar":"البَهْرَمَانِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"finest kind of ruby"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carbuncle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said to be brought from Sarandeeb [or Ceylon]: it has the property of exhilarating, and of conjoining [separated friends]; (TA;) and is profitable for disturbance of the mind (occasioned by the black bile, TA) and palpitation, and weakness of the heart and stomach, if drunk; [being app. reduced to powder for that purpose, as is done with some other gems in the East;] and for congealment of the blood, if hung [upon the person]: (K:) it is a Persian word, (S,) arabicized: (S, K:) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEuwlN","text_ar":"فَاعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawAqiytu","text_ar":"يَواقِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","S"]}]}}